Manchester City now have 14 backroom staff and seven first-team players isolating due to Covid-19; Burnley also revealed manager Sean Dyche will miss their tie at home to Huddersfield Town after he tested positive for Covid-19 The City manager recorded a positive test on Tuesday along with assistant Juanma Lillo. Both are now isolating, along with a number of other positive cases within the first team bubble, Man City confirmed. Guardiola Beats Klopp, Steven Gerrard To 10th Premier League… Pep Guardiola Facing Goalkeeping Crisis As Man City Duo Jet Off… The club now have 14 backroom staff and seven first-team players isolating due to Covid-19. Earlier on Thursday, Burnley revealed manager Sean Dyche will miss their tie at home to Huddersfield Town after he tested positive for Covid-19.